This is a draft that later become some changelog history for users. But now it like 'TODO-list'.

1) Unicode support.

    1.0) Linux system will use UTF-8 and Windows will use UTF-16LE (native 2bytes);

    1.1) Language files will be common for systems in UTF-8 (with conversions for windows).

2) FileList

    2.1) now not limited to 256 items!

    2.2) recursive subdirecories search support (?)

    2.3) fast search (like in FireFox)

    2.4) Randomizer

3) New OpenGL2/3 support??

4) Video with modules for FFDshow / DirectShow playback support

5) Picture support

    5.1) Now without DevIL library - each format will be supported naturally (with original free libraries like libpng);

    5.2) Add save and convert features (input -> output formats, color adjust, separation adjust) with preview window;

    5.3) Add GIF-2-samples support;

    5.4) Add

6) Modular architecture

    6.1) libStProperties for program properties;

    6.2) libStOutput for core output functions, that used with output-plugins;
         each plugin must have some check for harware support (for automatic plugin-choise)

        6.3.1) libStPageFlip for classic PageFlip and maybe blueline codes / DDS(?) as options;
        6.3.2) libStIZ3D for iZ3D monitors, need improvments from old code for speed and Linux support;
        6.3.3) libStInterlace for Interlace output to be NEW;
        6.3.4) libStAnaglyph for Anaglyph output, need improvments from old code;
        6.3.5) libStQuadBuffer for QuadBuffered output;
        6.3.6) libStVR920 *** ;
        6.3.7) libStDLP *** TOBEDO (checkmate) ;

    6.3) libStInput for input must support per-picture / per-video / stream (unlimited);
         base mechanism for buffers filling / modifications (save / capture / convert) used with input-plugins;

10) Threading

    10.1) On windows callback must be done in second thread than OpenGL-drawing
          (for non-stop playback, maybe SoftPageFlip will work better);

11) Vista/Win7 support

    11.1) Add digital signing (simplest, just for to be);
    11.2) UAC manifests;

12) Interface

    12.1) Optimized for current usage (sView, sPlay(?));
    12.2) Localized (non windows-rc-file mechanism).
    12.3) Improve Keyboard usage
        12.3.1) Add multimedia keys support;

    12.4) Add mouse usage
        12.4.1) Scrolling for 'zooming on area';
        12.4.2) 'Hand-tool';
        12.4.3) Right-click fast-options menu;
        12.4.4) DragNDrop support;

    12.5) Configuring program
        12.5.1) Add configuration-window;
        12.5.2) Add wizard for simple stereo-output choise;

    12.6) Thrumbul view support;
    12.7) Only-one-instance support

13) Spectogram / Visualizations for Audio playback

Compiler options:

    1) VC (PSDK)

        /EHsc - disable warning about 'C++ exception handler used, but unwind semantics are not enabled'
        /MP - add multi process compiling
        /W4 - warning level

Global defines:

    1) VC (PSDK)

        UNICODE // unicode support (use W versions for common functions)
        _CRT_SECURE_NO_WARNINGS // disable sprintf non secure functions warnings
        NDEBUG // not Debug

